Usage: main.py [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...

  Puppeteering tool for animatronics.

Options:
  -p  --play projectname [start_from]
                        Playback of every servo in projectname and,
                        if existent, audio, from startpoint [start_from]

  -sp --singleplay projectname channelfilename [audiofilename]
                        Playback of one specific servo though a specific servo. Optional audioplayback.

  -r  --record projectname channelfilename [audiofilename]
                        Record channelfilename. Optional specific audio playback with [audiofilename] (if none is entered, first in folder
                        will play if existent).

  -ss --setservo projectname channelfilename
			            Set config file for channelfilename in project - MCPin, servo_pin, map_min, map_max, start_pos

  -c  --connection projectname
                        Set connection type (USB/MCP3008).

  -n  --new projectname	Create new project structure.

  -cp  --copy projectname channelfilename_old channelfilename_new [True|False|servo_pin_new]
                        Duplicate channel_old to channel_new and copy config data associated with channel_old.
                        Servo_pin gets either copied [True/empty], gets incremented by total channels +1 [False] or gets
                        user defined by integer value [servo_pin_new].

  -ls --list [projectname]
                        List evey project (or a specific one with [projectname]) and every channel with their
                        servo-hat-pin-associations. Point out difficulties like multiple use of servo_pin or missing
                        files or config data.

  -cc --copyright       Show copyright infos.

  -h  --help            Show this message and exit.


Usage: waldo.py [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...
  -cal  --calibrate	reset and recalibrate buttons


GENERAL:
	Connect ethernet cable with "keyboard" attached before running waldo.py (e.g., startup). If you changed the length of the cable,
	run command "python waldo.py -cal". Restart.